prompt.preamble:
We are testing a system for understanding people's interest in reading different kinds of online articles.
For example, you might be interested in articles about some topics, but not about others.
prompt.task_description: your preferences of what kinds of online articles you would like to read
prompt.final: In the final part of the study, you will give feedback on a test set of article headline and descriptions, which will enable us to see how well a chatbot reading your responses has learned what you like and dislike.
prompt.evaluation: Please indicate whether you would like to read the following articles: "yes" if you would, "no" if you would not.

conversation_history.message: Okay if I'm clicking on an article it is usually some kind of news topic, I'm interested in news in many different areas like the economy, politics, technology, and video games.  I'm zero percent interested in celebrity news or gossip it is possibly my least favorite thing on the planet listening to the latest celebrity scandal.  I'm interested in multiple different view points when it comes to things like politics I would read multiple different articles from different sources if it is a consequential issue so that I have a better grasp on the issue and I'm not seeing the story through only one political lens.  I would rank my interests first politics/ world news, next technology, next economy, next video games/ entertainment.
